Some suggestions that you may or may not want to include.  These come from 
my designing of a distributed system...

Assuming that the goal is for the network XML to be transmitted to someone 
for evaluation, it might be useful to have an experiment ID, a generation 
ID, and an organism ID.  That way, when returning the evaluation results, it 
can return it to a single point of contact that then knows where to put 
them.  Then, it won&#39;t be necessary for the server to maintain a list of who 
took what and then run the risk of getting things confused.

It&#39;s just an idea, though.  :)


