&gt;Okay...here&#39;s my suggested format for network XML.
&gt;(I&#39;m using Colin&#39;s recent recurrent XOR network as an
&gt;example):
&gt;
&gt;&lt;network&gt;
&gt;   &lt;title&gt;Colin&#39;s XOR Network&lt;/title&gt;
&gt;   &lt;neuron id=&quot;0&quot; type=&quot;in&quot; hint-layer=&quot;1&quot;
&gt;hint-position=&quot;1&quot; /&gt;
&gt;   &lt;neuron id=&quot;1&quot; type=&quot;in&quot; hint-layer=&quot;1&quot;
&gt;hint-position=&quot;2&quot; /&gt;
&gt;   &lt;neuron id=&quot;2&quot; type=&quot;in&quot; hint-layer=&quot;1&quot;
&gt;hint-position=&quot;3&quot; /&gt;
&gt;   &lt;neuron id=&quot;3&quot; type=&quot;out&quot; hint-layer=&quot;2&quot;
&gt;hint-position=&quot;1&quot; /&gt;
&gt;   &lt;connection id=&quot;4&quot; src-id=&quot;0&quot; tgt-id=&quot;3&quot;
&gt;recurrent=&quot;false&quot; weight=&quot;1.64327624043105&quot; /&gt;
&gt;   &lt;connection id=&quot;5&quot; src-id=&quot;1&quot; tgt-id=&quot;3&quot;
&gt;recurrent=&quot;false&quot; weight=&quot;-3.3017311279049&quot; /&gt;
&gt;   &lt;connection id=&quot;6&quot; src-id=&quot;2&quot; tgt-id=&quot;3&quot;
&gt;recurrent=&quot;false&quot; weight=&quot;-3.3025163810043&quot; /&gt;
&gt;   &lt;connection id=&quot;7&quot; src-id=&quot;3&quot; tgt-id=&quot;3&quot;
&gt;recurrent=&quot;true&quot; weight=&quot;-7.44947553716588&quot; /&gt;
&gt;   &lt;/network&gt;
&gt;
&gt;Neurons need to have a layer designation, denoted by
&gt;the &quot;hint-layer&quot; attribute, and a position within that
&gt;layer, denoted by the &quot;hint-position&quot; attribute.  This
&gt;way, you can use whatever logic you like to place
&gt;neurons in any given layer and position, and the XSL
&gt;style sheet can just handle laying them out and
&gt;graphing them.
&gt;
&gt;Note that connections need to have an id, as well as a
&gt;&quot;recurrent&quot; attribute.
&gt;
&gt;I&#39;ll write a second XSL style sheet to handle the
&gt;transformation from this XML into a form that my
&gt;current style sheet can parse into an SVG image.
&gt;Again, all you&#39;ll need to do is make sure your XML is
&gt;in the above format, that all the files are in the
&gt;same directory, that you have Xalan and an SVG plug-in
&gt;installed, and then type &quot;draw [xml-filename]&quot;.
